    Ned Tijdschr Geneeskd. 2007 Sep 8;151(36):1987-93.

On hospital admission, older people generally have various, interacting comorbid 
conditions and an increased risk of fatal or nearly fatal events. This complex 
presentation necessitates a patient-centred healthcare instead of the initiation 
of various non-integrated disease strategies along the lines ofthe traditional 
(sub-)specialties. An international comparison of life expectancy after age 65 
shows that the Netherlands is progressively lagging behind other European 
countries and countries elsewhere in the world. This observation indicates a 
